{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01SBRKyfDFxuLekCGBg5YyUY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01URaHoioSQgX7DEvPdKsifu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(11d): release-gate preflight + crate publish metadata\n\nAdds scripts/verify-release-gates.sh — the entry gate to Tier 1 of the\nrelease publish chain. Enforces (in order, fail-fast):\n\n  1. GITHUB_REF_NAME matches v<axis-W-version> and the bare version\n     equals Cargo.toml [workspace.package].version.\n  2. scripts/set-version.sh --check-files passes (delegates the\n     two-axis drift checks landed in 11c).\n  3. HEAD is reachable from main (overridable via env for tests).\n  4. CHANGELOG.md has a \"## <version>\" section heading for the tag.\n  5. Every publishable workspace crate has description, license,\n     and repository populated in [package]. license/repository are\n     inherited from [workspace.package]; description is per-crate.\n\nPopulates the missing `description` field on the seven publishable\ncrates (fathomdb, fathomdb-cli, fathomdb-embedder,\nfathomdb-embedder-api, fathomdb-engine, fathomdb-query,\nfathomdb-schema) so check 5 passes on a clean tree.\n\nTest coverage in scripts/tests/test_verify_release_gates.sh — one\npositive + one negative per check, with file-snapshot restore so the\nsuite never leaves the worktree dirty. Wired into agent-test.sh.\n\nOwner: dev/design/release.md § Tiered publish order.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit verify-release-gates + descriptions"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":379,"cache_read_input_tokens":93858,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":379},"output_tokens":57,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,