{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_0156C9UeAkgp9NAJZKizoRNH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JS4XXFA3kUGePUeHjYushH","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(11d): post-publish smoke scripts per AC-056\n\nAdds three smoke scripts under scripts/release/smoke/ — the gate that\nproves a published artifact actually installs and runs cleanly on a\nfresh machine, distinct from the CI build which only proves the\nworkspace compiles. Per feedback_release_verification: green CI +\npublished artifact is NOT done.\n\n  smoke-crates-cli.sh:  cargo install fathomdb-cli --version $1\n                        → fathomdb doctor check-integrity --json\n                        → jq parses output. Engine::open creates the\n                        DB file lazily, so no init verb required.\n  smoke-pypi-wheel.sh:  fresh venv + pip install fathomdb==$1\n                        → Engine.open + write + search + close\n                        → python process exits 0.\n  smoke-npm-package.sh: fresh npm init + npm install fathomdb@$1\n                        → Engine.open + write + search + close\n                        → node process exits 0.\n\nEach script: `set -euo pipefail`, semver regex guard on $1 before any\nnetwork call, mktemp -d fixture dir, EXIT trap for cleanup,\nversion-pinned install command.\n\nTest coverage in scripts/tests/test_smoke_scripts.sh is STRUCTURAL,\nnot integration — running real installs against real registries would\nneed network, the artifact existing at the test version, and tens of\nseconds of wall time per script. Header comment documents the\nrationale. Wired into agent-test.sh.\n\nOwner: dev/design/release.md § Post-publish smoke.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit smoke scripts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":525,"cache_re