{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_011XB9CqYpNgX73XY9BBLmRY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JjUkPihzEE2fd2gFdFgUEA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add Cargo.toml scripts/set-version.sh scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh src/rust/crates/*/Cargo.toml && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfix(11d): version pins for in-workspace deps + set-version coverage\n\nBlocker surfaced by `cargo publish --dry-run -p fathomdb-engine`:\n\n  error: failed to verify manifest at fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml\n  Caused by: all dependencies must have a version requirement specified\n  when publishing. dependency `fathomdb-embedder-api` does not specify a\n  version\n\ncargo strips `path = ...` at publish time and resolves siblings through\nthe registry, so every in-workspace dep needs a version requirement —\nwithout it, T4 (engine) and every later tier would fail at actual tag\ntime even though local `cargo build` is happy.\n\nAdds [workspace.dependencies] to Cargo.toml with one centralized pin\nper sibling (Axis W for fathomdb / fathomdb-embedder / fathomdb-engine\n/ fathomdb-query / fathomdb-schema; Axis E for fathomdb-embedder-api).\nEach crate's `[dependencies]` switches its in-workspace deps to\n`<crate>.workspace = true`, so the version flows from one source.\n\nscripts/set-version.sh:\n  --workspace <v>     now also rewrites every Axis-W\n                      [workspace.dependencies] pin to <v>.\n  --embedder-api <v>  now also rewrites the Axis-E\n                      [workspace.dependencies] pin to <v>.\n  --check-files       gains a per-pin axis-match check with the same\n                      `<file>:<line>: version drift — observed/expected`\n                      diagnostic shape as the other checks.\n\nscripts/tests/test_set_version.sh: +3 tests covering the new behaviors\n(drift on a pin, --embedder-api propagation to the Axis-E pin,\n--workspace propagation across every Axis-W pin while leaving Axis E\nalone).\n\n`bash scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` is clean on the new state.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit manifest + set-version fix"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":177404,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":62,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c2ab885-f26f-4687-8076-7a046130c523","uuid":"71a0d880-d932-4d88-a816-8218aec87ccb"}
